se conditions? I'm on insulin for diabetes. Um, I'm on Ramipro for high blood pressure and I'm also insulin for diabetes. I'm on Ramipro for high blood pressure, and I'm also on a statin for the cholesterol. Okay. And do you have any allergies to medications? No. All right. And have you had any surgeries in the past? No. All right. And are your immunizations up to date? I think so. All right. And can you tell me a little bit about your living situation currently, like who you're living with and whereabouts? I live with my husband in a house downtown. Okay. And are you working currently? No, I retired early. Okay. And do you drink alcohol? I'll have a glass of wine every night. Okay, so about seven drinks per week? Yes. Okay, and do you smoke cigarettes? No, I don't. All right, and how about the use of any recreational drugs like cannabis or anything else? No. All right. And is there any, like, musculoskeletal or, like, autoimmune conditions that run in the family? No musculoskeletal issues. I know diabetes runs in the family. Okay. All right. So that was everything I wanted to ask on history. So next, I just wanted to do a physical exam. And just looking at the left knee, are you seeing any swelling or redness on the knee? It appears slightly more swollen than my right knee. Okay. Are you seeing any redness? No redness. Okay. And are there any temperature changes? like does the knee feel hot or or warm no okay and if you um press along the uh uh joint line do you feel any pain um yeah it feels a little tender okay And how about pain over any of the muscles, like the thigh muscles or the hamstrings or the calf muscles? No, those are fine. Okay. And then how about any pain over the patella or kneecap? Um, that's a little bit more painful. Okay. Um, and are you able to bend your knee, uh, like, like flex it, um, and straighten it? Uh, I can do that. It's just painful when I do that. Okay. Um, and, um, and then how about walking? Do you have an antalgic gait or a limp? 