␀","you tell me what brought you in today? Sure. So my son, he's two and a half months old and we're in the ER because he's had this cough, fever, it seems like he's breathing too fast. It's been happening for the past two days and we weren't sure what else to do for him. Okay. So the first thing here would be like vital signs and assessing kind of stability. So is there that information? We're going to say vital stable. He is on two liters of oxygen right now. okay um so when did uh stable. He is on two liters of oxygen right now. Okay. So, when did the symptoms specifically start? Two days ago. Okay. And what started first? um so i guess he was coughing first and then we took his temperature and it seemed like he had a fever it was over 38 um and then over the past couple of hours it seems like he's having a hard time breathing he's breathing too fast okay so um so with this cough, has there, has it been, any sputum come up? Yes, yeah, yellow sputum. Yellow, okay. Any blood that you've noticed in the sputum? No. Okay, and how was the fever checked? We did a rectal. Okay. And has the temperature, like, has there been a fever the entire time? We checked twice. We checked on the first day and then again last night okay um and in regards to the difficulties breathing uh has there been any like changes to um like has there been any noisy breathing um i would say he sounds slightly wheezy. Okay. Have you been hearing any, like, whistling sounds when he's breathing in? I wouldn't say whistling. No, no. Okay. And has he been experiencing any other symptoms? Um, no, uh, has, has he been experiencing any other symptoms? Um, no, he actually, he hasn't gone through as many wet diapers as he normally does. Okay. Um, has he been, uh, well, how's his appetite been? Um, not the greatest, no no okay so not not eating um not eating as much or drinking as much yeah okay uh how how has his behavior been oh he's been very very fussy okay inconsolable would you say? Yes, yeah. Okay, and any bowel problems? No, not that we noticed. Okay, and any vomiting? No. Okay, um and uh have you guys been around any anybody who's been sick no okay so everybody else has been been well uh any travel uh recently um we haven't traveled recently um my mom so so his grandma, had traveled recently, and he saw her last week. Okay. Where did she go? Mexico. Okay. And how's grandma doing now? She's doing fine. Yeah. Okay. And he spent some time with her? Mm-hmm. He spent the day with her. Okay. I see. And so in regards to past health, has he had any symptoms like this before? I guess last month he kind of had similar symptoms and they said it was a viral infection. So he was just given some puffers to help us breathing and he got better on his own. Okay. Did they tell you what the diagnosis was at that time or just say that it was a viral infection? No, they said it could be bronchiolitis or just an upper viral infection. Okay. Any reasons for hospitalizations? At that time that he had the bronchiolitis or viral infection, he was hospitalized for two days just to help his breathing. Okay. Um, and, um, any, any medications that he takes regularly or uses regularly? Uh, he, no, no. Okay. Any, uh, allergies to medications that you're aware of no okay and um in regards to um birthing or prenatal history were there any complications throughout pregnancy no I wouldn't say so no it was normal everything was normal and he was a healthy baby okay um and uh has and, uh, has mom had any, uh, complications with any prior pregnancies? No, he's, uh, he's the first one. He's the first one. Okay. Um, and, uh, was mom well throughout the pregnancy, like no infectious symptoms, uh, during? No, no. Okay. Um, and any concerns with, um, his growth or, or development so far? No, he's been a normal. Okay. And then any concerns with, uh, either his vision or, uh, or hearing? No. Are his immunizations up to date? Yes, they are. Okay. Could you tell me a little bit about the living situation? You know what I mean? up-to-date? Yes, they are. Okay. Could you tell me a little bit about the living situation? Who's in the home currently and where you guys are living? Yeah, so we live in a house. It's him, myself, and my husband, his dad. Okay. Any pets at home? No pets, no actually goldfish oh cool um and um are there any concerns for uh um like uh verbal abuse in the home no how about any physical abuse in the home? No. Okay. And does anybody smoke cigarettes in the home? No. Okay. And then how about drink alcohol? We have like a glass of wine once a week. Okay. Um, and who's the, uh, primary, uh, caregiver for him? I guess, uh, we both are. Um, yeah, we both are. Okay. Um, and, uh, in the family, are there any, uh, lung conditions like asthma or, um, any heart conditions that, that run in the family, are there any lung conditions like asthma or any heart conditions that run in the family? My sister, so his aunt, has asthma. Okay. And does anybody, is there any congenital diseases that run in the family? No, no. Okay. How about any genetic diseases? No. Okay. Okay. Um, and, um, so, um, it's sounding like, um, we wanted to do a workup for his symptoms right now for breathing heavily and with the fever that's concerning for a type of infection. and with being under three months, it would warrant some investigations. So we'd want to check, do some blood tests and check his cerebrospinal fluid as well to make sure that there's no infection in the brain, I guess and um we'll kind of go go from there sure yeah that sounds good okay um in the meantime yeah we'll give you some um inhalers and keep the oxygen on to help uh with the lungs um and the breathing and then keep monitoring for um uh how he's doing uh symptomatically okay thank you uh you're welcome were there any uh was there anything else that i i missed to ask about uh no i don't think so okay oh that sounds good so if there was nothing else that you wanted to share we'll get that started and I'll be back shortly okay sounds good thank you",1.0370036101083033,1.0,1.0,41,0,1108,0
RES0003,"D: It's nice to meet you. What's your name? 

P: It's nice to meet you as well. My name is Jenn and I'm here with my son Joey here, who he's had a sore throat now for the last couple of days. 

D: OK, how old is he, Joey? 

P: Uh, he is 3 years old. 

D: He's three years old, OK. And you said for the past couple days, so about 2-3 days?

P: Yeah, probably yeah about 3 days ago he he didn't go to school for the last two days because, or I mean daycare I should say because the pains but was bugging him so bad.

D: OK, yeah um. So how long has he been going to daycare for?

P: He started this year, so, um, he's been going for about six months. 

D: OK? Is he having issues swallowing food? Does it hurt when he swallows food?

P: Yeah, he's, uh, he's definitely the last couple of days hasn't been eating as much like solid food. He's drinking cold liquids okay but yeah, he hasn't been eating as much. 

D: OK. 

P: He says it's hard to. He does say it hurts to swallow as well.

