pposed to night uh it's pretty it's pretty uh bad all day actually and um it's been impacting my sleep because I've been coughing at night too i see and um in terms of uh things that make it worse anything you do around the house or at work that makes the coughing worse uh yeah i guess if i'm um just moving around a little bit more it it might bring it on a little bit more, but it's pretty bad all day. I see. And in terms of any other symptoms you might be having, do you have any shortness of breath, runny nose, any chest pain? Um, no, not really. Okay. Besides the pink-tinged sputum, have you ever coughed up blood, like red blood? Not anything that was really bright red. More pink. More pink? Okay. Yeah, so you traveled to India just two months ago. Do you remember what kind of place you stayed in in India? Was it a crowded place, or were you by yourself? Well, I mean, there was a lot of people around. Yeah was not a lot of uh room where i was was staying so um it was pretty crowded okay and was there anyone that was ill around you or any exposure to tuberculosis um not that i'm aware of. I was around my family, um, but, um, I guess it's possible. Okay. And once you came back, uh, did anyone else, um, in your family, uh, get sick or was it just you? uh yeah I spoke to my relative when I got back and they did tell me about one of my cousins there that was feeling sick. Okay. And have you been having any fevers or chills? Yeah, I feel like I've been pretty hot sometimes. Okay. And how about night sweats? Yeah, the cough's been messing with my sleep, but I've been waking up with night sweats. Okay. And have you been having any headaches uh no headaches any do you feel uh that you've lost any weight recently uh maybe a few pounds but um have you tried to lose weight or was that unintentional? No, I was kind of surprised. I thought I would have gained weight because I've been a bit more lazy recently, but the weight seems to be down anyway. I see. Okay. Have you noticed any wheezing sounds when you breathe out or breathe in? No wheezing. Okay. And you mentioned no chest pain, right? Yeah, no chest pain. Okay. Have you noticed any kind of swelling in your legs or hands or anywhere else in your body? No swelling. Okay. Any bowel movement changes, any constipation or diarrhea? Neither of those. Okay. Any urinary problems? No. Okay. Any changes in your appetite at all? Do you feel that you've lost any appetite? Yeah, maybe eating a little bit less. Okay. And in your current environment right now, are you exposed to any fumes or dust or any animals? Um, we have a dog, but no fumes or anything like that. Okay. Have you experienced any kind of dizziness or fainting spells? Nope. Okay. In terms of your past medical history, have you been diagnosed with any medical conditions? um yeah i've had, high blood pressure, um, uh, type two diabetes and, uh, high cholesterol. And are you taking any medications for any of those? Yeah, I'm taking, um, uh, a few medications for, uh, blood pressure and, um, uh, and, and diabetes right now. And I think, uh, resupostatin for, for the, the cholesterol. I'm not sure of the other ones though. Okay. No worries. And do you know if you're allergic to any medications or do you have any environmental allergies? Uh, I think I, I got a rash to penicillin, uh, when Iillin when I was younger, but that's it. Okay. Any previous hospitalizations? Nope. Any surgeries? No surgeries. Okay. And your family, has anyone ever had any cancers or died of a heart attack? Um, yeah, my mother had a heart attack when she was, uh, 48. Okay. And has anyone ever had, um, anything like pulmonary fibrosis or any autoimmune conditions? What are those? So pulmonary fibrosis is a condition in your lung where you start getting like these nodules and it can run in the family. I see. That can cause some of the symptoms like a chronic cough it can cause sometimes shortness of breath and it can sometimes be associated with like some connective 