n with swallowing food or liquids? No. Okay. And have you had any fevers or chills? No. Or any night sweats? No. And any changes to your weight recently? um i've had some weight gain over the past like six months okay oh that's great and how about how much uh just maybe like five ten pounds five to ten pound somewhere around there. Okay, well, that's good. And have you had any nausea or vomiting? No. And how about any abdominal pain? No. Any diarrhea? No. Or any urinary problems no No. Have you had any muscle aches or joint pains? No. Okay. And have you had any loss of your taste or sense of smell? No. Okay. Okay. And any skin changes or rashes um nope nothing like that okay uh and um so you've been experiencing so you had a runny nose that's gone away um and now you've been having this cough for the past dry cough the past three days and lost your voice yesterday. Have you been experiencing any other symptoms? No, no other symptoms. All right. In the past, have you been diagnosed with any medical conditions? No, I've been pretty healthy. that's great. And have you had any allergies before? No. Okay. And do you take any medications regularly? I just take some multivitamins. Okay. And are you aware if your immunizations are up to date? So I have everything except for that HPV vaccine. Okay. Do you have a plan to get that one? I think so. I just uh waiting to follow up with um my family doctor about that okay no that's a good idea for sure so uh it's great that you have a plan for that um for that um as it can yeah it can be really helpful for uh cervical cancer as, as I'm sure you'll talk to, uh, with a family doctor about, um, yeah. Um, and have you had any hospitalizations or any surgeries? Uh, no. Okay. And, uh, whereabouts are you living right now and who are you living with? I live with my parents and my two younger siblings. We live in a house. Has anybody else been sick or have similar symptoms? No, no one at home has been sick. Okay. And how about anybody at school or work or anything like that that you've been around who's been sick? So one of my friends actually had a runny nose and a cough as well a couple of days ago, but she seems to be better now and her voice is okay okay and um have you traveled anywhere outside of the city or province no no not recently all right and But in the home, is there any like are you exposed to any violence of any sort, like physical or emotional, either yourself or or witnessing? No. OK. And what grade are you in? I'm in grade seven or yeah, grade seven now. Oh, awesome. And what grade are you in? I'm in grade seven or yeah, grade seven now. Oh, awesome. And is there any smoking in the home? No, no one smokes at home. Okay. And then anybody in the family have any heart or lung conditions? Heart or lung? I know, like, heart disease runs on my father's side of the family. I'm not really sure, like, exactly what kind of disease is, though okay um and oh i remember sometimes people uh kind of in this age group might experience with either drugs or alcohol have your friends done that or or yourself um i know like some of my friends have uh tried alcohol and tried marijuana, but I haven't experimented yet. Okay, that's good. And that's all I wanted to ask today on history. Was there anything else that you wanted to add? Well, nothing that I to add i just uh what do you how do you think i can make this make my voice better and um how long will i have have this hoarse voice yeah so um right now it's sounding like um a a viral type illness where there's inflammation of the vocal cords with having a cough and the runny nose a couple of days ago. And actually, this reminds me that I'm not sure if I asked about fevers or chills, if you have any. No, I haven't. Okay. And so if it is a viral infection, then it's just supportive kind of management. So that will mean trying to stay as hydrated as you possibly can over these next um next few days and then also you can uh use things like if they help l